CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 21, 1955, pg. 17 reads: "Noon Survey - James T. Goode tells his running mate, George G. Hill, that chances of victory look good-at noon on Tuesday. Goode was a candidate for constable and Hill aspired to the alderman's post.  They ran second to Harry B. Fitzgerald and Thomas J. Smith. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: George G. Hill talking to runningmate James T. Goode holding document, on street with apartment building in background, during 1955 primary elections
